reviewText: This course offers a great overview of Immigration Law. I like the flexibility of the course, since you can essentially learn at your own pace and receive the certificate of completion immediately after submitting the final quiz. This course is a good introduction for those who have little to no background knowledge on the subject matter. The instructor clearly explains the material and provides good examples to help make sure you can retain it. Additionally, the supplemental material (reading) that is provided contains good additional details to know for each section.
Easy to pay attention to the classes. Great examples and metaphors by the professor.

Thank you so much for covering all the visa categories and detail with very basic examples. It was very helpful and  easy to understand, complete all the modules.

Immigration may seem like a simple way to go to America. I started following this course at a relatively late age, and I think that I wasted a lot of this age without learning. I wish I had enough time to study more about these practical laws, and perhaps one day visit America, the country of immigrant.
